<strong></strong>
</p>
<p>
We adjust to every patient's needs and may offer hypnotherapy (therapeutic hypnosis) if we feel this approach will be of benefit to them. Among the many
schools of psychotherapy, hypnotherapy stands out for various reasons:
<br/>
<br/>
<br/>
</p>
<ul type="disc">
<li>
It combines the access to unconscious mental processes, obtained through the hypnotic state, and the possibility to take action on those processes
while in this modified state of consciousness. This method is particularly interesting as it is a<strong><u>brief therapy</u></strong>: the person only
needs a limited number of sessions before he/she can start to feel the effect of the intervention, which is not the case in most other types of
therapy. It is possible to treat light to moderate psychological issues without a deep root cause in less than 5 sessions. For moderate to more severe
issues or to treat problems that have been with the person most of their life, they may consider to spend at least 5-10 sessions.
</li>
</ul>
<ul type="disc">
<li>
Hypnotherapy is particularly useful to treat        <strong>anxiety-related issues, stress, stuttering, tobacco addiction, some phobias, weight loss, migraines, trauma</strong> etc… It can also be used
to treat <strong>lack of confidence, exam preparation, an important decision to make</strong> etc…
</li>
</ul>
<ul type="disc">
<li>
Any problem involving a person’s mind or emotions can be relieved through therapeutic hypnosis. However, physical impairment is not an indication for
hypnotherapy, except as a psychological support method when combined with a medical approach.
</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br/>
Hypnotherapy is indicated for <strong>children, adolescents, adults and couples</strong>.
